.wH .in  
.VL  
.LI "\*LXmNactivateCallback\*O"
Specifies the list of callbacks
that is called when the PushButtonGadget is activated.
It is activated when the user presses
and releases the active mouse button while the
pointer is inside
the PushButtonGadget.  Activating PushButtonGadget
also disarms it.
For this callback the reason is \*LXmCR_ACTIVATE\*O.
.LI "\*LXmNarmCallback\*O"
Specifies the list of callbacks
that is called when PushButtonGadget is armed.
It is armed when the user presses the active
mouse button while the pointer is inside the PushButtonGadget.
For this callback the reason is \*LXmCR_ARM\*O.
.LI "\*LXmNarmColor\*O"
Specifies the color with which to fill the armed button.
\*LXmNfillOnArm\*O must be set to True for this resource to have an effect.
The default for a color display is a color between the background and the
bottom shadow color.  For a monochrome display, the default is set to the
foreground color, and any text in the label appears in the background
color when the button is armed.
.LI "\*LXmNarmPixmap\*O"
Specifies the pixmap to be used as the button face if \*LXmNlabeltype\*O is
\*LXmPIXMAP\*O and PushButtonGadget is armed.
This resource is disabled when the PushButtonGadget is in a menu.
.LI "\*LXmNdefaultButtonShadowThickness\*O"
This resource specifies the width of the default button indicator shadow.
If this resource is zero, the width of the shadow comes from the value of
the \*LXmNshowAsDefault\*O resource.  If this resource is greater than
zero, the \*LXmNshowAsDefault\*O resource is only used to specify whether
this button is the default.
The default value is the initial value of \*LXmNshowAsDefault\*O.
.LI "\*LXmNdisarmCallback\*O"
Specifies the list of callbacks
that is called when the PushButtonGadget is disarmed.
PushButtonGadget is disarmed when the user presses and releases the
active mouse button while the pointer is inside that
gadget.
For this callback, the reason is \*LXmCR_DISARM\*O.
.LI "\*LXmNfillOnArm\*O"
Forces the PushButtonGadget to fill the background of the button with the
color specified by \*LXmNarmColor\*O when the button is armed and when this
resource is set to True.  If False, only the top and bottom
shadow colors are
switched.  When the PushButtonGadget is in a menu, this resource is ignored
and assumed to be False.
.LI "\*LXmNmultiClick\*O"
If a button click is followed by another button click within the time
span specified by the display's multi-click time, and this resource is
set to \*LXmMULTICLICK_DISCARD\*O, do not process the second click.
If this resource is set to \*LXmMULTICLICK_KEEP\*O, process the event
and increment \*Vclick_count\*O in the callback structure.
When the button is in a menu, the default is \*LXmMULTICLICK_DISCARD\*O;
otherwise, for a button not in a menu \*LXmMULTICLICK_KEEP\*O is
the default value.
.LI "\*LXmNshowAsDefault\*O"
If \*LXmNdefaultButtonShadowThickness\*O is greater than zero, a value
greater than zero in this resource
specifies to mark this button as the default button.
If \*LXmNdefaultButtonShadowThickness\*O is zero, a value greater than
zero in this resource specifies to mark this button as the default
button with the shadow thickness specified by this resource.
The space between
the shadow and the default shadow is equal to the sum of both shadows.
The default value is zero.  When this value is not zero, the Label
resources \*LXmNmarginLeft\*O, \*LXmNmarginRight\*O, \*LXmNmarginTop\*O, and
\*LXmNmarginBottom\*O may be modified to accommodate the second shadow.
This resource is disabled when the PushButton is in a menu.
